The files in this folder are all outcomes from idr.conservative_peak by HALPER

The files that can be used are all in narrowPeak
*There are all in human genome coordination*

human_conservative.sorted.narrowPeak: the original human idr.conservative_peak
human_specific_peaks_constervative.narrowPeak: the human specific region
mouse_specific_peaks_constervative.narrowPeak: the mouse specific region in human coordination
shared_peaks_conservative.narrowPeak: the shared region
mouse_to_human_conservative.narrowPeak: mouse mapped to human genome coordination
mouse_specific_peaks_constervative.mouse_coords.narrowPeak: the mouse specific region in mouse coordination

For human_conservative.sorted.narrowPeak and human_specific_peaks_constervative.narrowPeak:
narrowPeak columns (BED6 + 4)
#	Column name	Description
1	chrom	Chromosome name (e.g., chr1)
2	chromStart	Start position (0-based)
3	chromEnd	End position (1-based)
4	name	Peak name (often . or ID)
5	score	Integer score (0–1000, for visualization)
6	strand	Strand (. for ATAC/ChIP usually)
7	signalValue	Strength of signal (e.g., enrichment)
8	pValue	−log10(p-value)
9	qValue	−log10(q-value, FDR-adjusted)
10	peak	Offset of summit from start

However, for mouse_specific_peaks_constervative.narrowPeak, shared_peaks_conservative.narrowPeak, mouse_to_human_conservative.narrowPeak
They will add the raw mouse coordination in col 4 and the col for scores, pValue can not be used, which need to attach to the raw mouse file.
